&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity for a qualified Psychological Wellbeing Therapist .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be a member of a multidisciplinary team (MDT) who deliver health service provisions to Marginalised &amp; Vulnerable Adults in Suffolk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be accountable for providing direct therapeutic interventions to Refugee &amp; Asylum Seeking clients; for this post the role includes both adults and children. The role will encompass both face-to-face interventions and use of varied technologies. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a new project with Health Outreach/EPUT working in partnership with the Wellbeing &amp; Work for Refugee Integration Project which is managed by the Strategic Migration Partnership.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who shares our Trust values of Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Kat Saunders Job title Psychological Wellbeing Therapist Email address kat.saunders@nhs.net Telephone number 01473 341763&lt;/p&gt;
